comment_text:
I know I'm late, but I also wanted to add that Du Maurier always insisted she didn't write romances. Rebecca is supposed to be a gothic horror/mindfuck. Du Maurier wasn't writing a love story.

&#x200B;

She was successful at itðŸ‘ I remember people finding it romantic. The idea of a young poor girl marrying a rich man. On the surface, it looks like a Cinderella story. I think it's a fractured fairytale and it works.  She doesn't really live or learn how to be/think independently. What do you think?
